──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HUMAN-WRITTEN TEXTS (data/human_texts.jsonl)
License: Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 (CC BY-SA 4.0)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Human-written texts are extracted from Persian Wikipedia revisions dated
before 31 December 2019. Wikipedia content is licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0,
and this dataset inherits that license for the human-text portion.

Full license text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/legalcode

When using these texts, you must:
  - Provide attribution to Persian Wikipedia
  - Distribute derivatives under the same CC BY-SA 4.0 license
  - Indicate if changes were made (the dataset preserves revid for traceability)

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
AI-GENERATED TEXTS (data/ai_texts.jsonl)
Terms: Provider-specific
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

AI-generated texts were produced through the AvalAI API using DeepSeek v3.1,
GPT-4o-mini, and Gemini 2.5 Flash-Lite. Each provider's terms of service
apply to the model outputs. This dataset is released for academic research
purposes only.

You are responsible for ensuring your use complies with:
  - OpenAI usage policies (for GPT-4o-mini outputs)
  - DeepSeek terms of service (for DeepSeek v3.1 outputs)
  - Google AI terms (for Gemini outputs)

